      },
      "date": "2012-07-18 08:27:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThere is one remaining possible problem - \"#include <../fs/mount.h>\".\n\nI think the main idea behind hiding vfsmount guts (move from\ninclude/linux/mount.h to fs/mount.h) seems to be it is not suggestted to access them above or within VFS layer.\n\nThere are some other kernel code inside \"fs\" directory also include fs/mount.h. So I think possibly it is not a big issue for lustre to include that file, as lustre will also be inside \"fs\" directory in the future.\n\nI am OK to combine this patch with http://review.whamcloud.com/1951 if needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
